[1]
Date: 25 Oct 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_41.HTM#Sec13>

Newcastle disease In Turkey
---------------------------
See also: 9 Dec 2005, 11 Nov 2005, 30, 16 and 9 Jul 2004
Information received on 9 Dec 2005 from Dr Nihat Pakdil, general director
of protection and control, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, Ankara:
End of previous report period: 8 Nov 2005 (see Disease Information 2005;
18[45]: 420, 11 Nov)
End of this report period: 8 Dec 2005.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 1 Nov 2005.
Date of start of the event: 20 Oct 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Details of the outbreak (reminder):
1st administrative division (province): Bursa
Lower administrative division (district): Inegol
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Akbaslar
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
816 / 120 / 120 / 696 / 0
Diagnosis (updated information):
Bornova Veterinary Control and Research Institute on 1 Nov 2005 conducted
virus isolation in embryonated chicken eggs (positive), hemagglutination
test (positive), and hemagglutination inhibition test (positive titre: 1/256).
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: contact with infected birds(s).
Control measures undertaken: vaccination against Newcastle disease was
recommended to all poultry farms in Inegol district.
Final report: yes.
Event ended: yes.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
